did.abstract:
Robert S. Sargent was an electrical engineer, Defense Department defensive weapons specialist, and published poet who lived most of his adult life in Washington, DC. He was born in New Orleans in 1912 and died in Washington, DC in 2006. He began writing poetry in his fifties.
This collection includes published and unpublished poetry, drafts, correspondence, and biographical materials related to the literary and personal life of poet Robert Sargent. The materials range in date from 1923-2006.

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: Robert S. Sargent was an electrical engineer, Defense Department defensive weapons specialist, and published poet who lived most of his adult life in Washington, DC. He was born in New Orleans in 1912, raised in Mississippi, and was a 1933 graduate of Mississippi State University. After serving in the Navy during World War II, he worked at the Pentagon from the late 1940s until 1972. During his time at the Pentagon he was the recipient of the Distinguished Civilian Service Award.

Sargent began writing poetry in his fifties and published 11 books of poetry: Now is Always the Miraculous Time (1977), A Woman from Memphis (1979), Aspects of a Southern Story (1983), Fish Galore (1989), The Cartographer (1994), Stealthy Days (1998), The Jazz Poems of Robert Sargent (2000), Altered in the Telling (2001),Wonderous News (2002), 99 After 80 (2003), and Lula and I (2004). Sargent's literary subjects included his family, the South, art, love, the Bible, and jazz. His poems were published in a number of literary journals, including Antioch Review, New York Quarterly, Georgia Review, Poetry Review, Prairie Schooner, Western Humanities Review and many others. His poems also appeared in a number of anthologies, including Poetry magazine's The Poetry Anthology.
Sargent died on April 24, 2006 in Washington after suffering a stroke.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series contains documents from Sargent's childhood, materials relating to his career as an engineer, an essay written by Sargent on special relativity, a travel notebook, and certificates from the Department of Defense. The materials range in date from 1923-1998.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Arranged alphabetically. Some folders appear to be out of alphabetical order. When this is the case it was as the donor intended.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series contains personal correspondence between Robert Sargent and his family, friends, fellow poets, musicians, and others. Of note is a letter Sargent wrote to Albert Einstein and Einstein's reply. The materials in this series range in date from 1933 - 2005.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Organized into four subseries: Poetry and other writings; Poetry reading supplements; Business records; and Published works.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series contains drafts and final copies of more than one hundred Robert Sargent's poems. It also contains records of and materials used for Sargent's public poetry readings and correspondence and records concering the publishing of Sargent's books. Finally, this series contains copies of poetry journals and anthologies in which Sargent's poetry is published. The materials in this series range in date from 1961-2006.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: The original order of this subseries has been maintained. The poetry has been arranged alphabetically first, with the other writings arranged alphabetically at the end.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This subseries contains drafts and final copies of over 100 of Robert Sargent's poems as well as essays and other unpublished poems.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This subseries contains copies of poems Robert Sargent read at various poetry readings throughout his career as well as correspondence regarding these readings. This subseries also includes slides that were used as part of the poetry presentations. The materials in this subseries range in date from Circa 1980 - 2003.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This subseries contains awards and media publicity about Robert Sargent's career as a poet. Records and correspondence regarding the publication of Sargent's books of poetry is also included in this suberies. The materials range in date from 1996-2006.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This subseries contains copies of poetry journals and other poetry publications in which Robert Sargent's poems were published. The materials range in date from 1961 - 2003.
